Content:: Historical Biology is a peer-reviewed scientific journal of paleobiology. It was established in 1988, and is published by Taylor & Francis. The journal is edited by Gareth J. Dyke (National Oceanography Centre). The journal is abstracted and indexed in the following databases.[1][2] According to the Journal Citation Reports, the journal has a 2020 impact factor of 2.259.
